    "note": "Past perfect with just / after / before (revision): had + past participle marks the EARLIER of two past actions; after + past perfect, before + past simple, by the time, just; sequencing vs past simple; connector meanings (reason / contrast / purpose). 34 vocab + 57 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 40 → 57 items / 10 formats). 4 verify lenses: answers + translation + register all found 0 defects (every sequence puts the past perfect on the earlier action; all connector classifications correct; German natural; no jargon). Fixes: relabeled the connector group-sort (German category nouns Grund/Gegensatz/Absicht → taught 'why?'/'but'/'what for?'); reworded mc.011 'Vergangenheit' + mt.002 'Grundform' out of prompts; fixed gf.016/gf.021 2-blank pipe answers ('had | cooked'); reworded eating-disorder def off its headword token ('eat'); granted the past-participle / irregular-past load that lands in gloss-less distractor & group-member sentences (gone/went/eaten/ate/left/won/win/practised/however/already/etc.) + natural/unhealthy; disambiguated cp.002 sentence-initial Sie→Lisa. The 31 inline glosses (food-domain + participle forms) are correct; 38 translation audits accurate (diet→Ernährung not the false-friend Diät; gym→Turnhalle PE-sense). 3 defensible explainDe sentence-initial-Sie warns (=she/they). Validate green."
